[129.588517, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe user wants a persistent agent `line-summarizer` that reads a file at a given path and \u001b[0m\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2msummarizes its contents in a single sentence. Per the authoring discipline: validate the \u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mdraft first (structural + collision + unknown-tools checks), then create. I already know \u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mfrom the prior turn that no user-defined agents exist, so no collision is expected. I'll \u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mdraft a focused instruction (role, decision flow, content-handling, safety) and a \u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mtool-context naming `read-file` (and `grep` for large files), then dry-run with \u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mmeta-agent$validate.\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mmeta-agent$validate\u001b[0m({\"name\" \"line-summarizer\", \"description\" \"Reads a file at...): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 3ms, 99 chars\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(37601 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(14.7s)\u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m"]
[129.588644, "o", "  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe dry-run (meta-agent$validate) passed cleanly: :valid true, :collision false, \u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m:instruction-ok true, :name-ok true, :unknown-tools [] (read-file and grep both resolve), \u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m:errors []. No existing agent to overwrite. Per the authoring discipline, the next step is \u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mmeta-agent$create with the same name/instruction/tool-context/description. I'll reuse the \u001b[0m\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mvalidated draft verbatim.\u001b[0m\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mmeta-agent$create\u001b[0m({\"name\" \"line-summarizer\", \"description\" \"Reads a file at...): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 6ms, 161 chars\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;96m+\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(38157 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(33.7s)\u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe dry-run validation passed cleanly and meta-agent$create succeeded, persisting the \u001b[0m\u001b[18;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2magent and registering user$agent$line-summarizer. The authoring discipline requires a \u001b[0m\u001b[19"]
[129.588903, "o", ";1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mVERIFY step: ask the new agent one representative question and confirm it answers \u001b[0m\u001b[20;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2msensibly. I'll point it at an existing project file (.brainyard/BRAINYARD.md) to confirm \u001b[0m\u001b[21;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mit reads a file and returns a single-sentence summary.\u001b[0m\u001b[22;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36muser$agent$line-summarizer\u001b[0m({:question \"Summarize the file at /Users/xroger88/Project...): called\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[1m\u001b[95m subagents (1 running, 0 done) \u001b[0m\u001b[2m───────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[1;96m●\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97muser$agent$line-summarizer/ivory-bear-1247\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m[user$agent$line-summarizer]\u001b[0m  \u001b[96mrunning\u001b[0m  \u001b[2mIter 2/100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(32946 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m20s\u001b[0m\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[1;93m○\u001b[0m \u001b[1mtask-2630\u001b[0m - \u001b[2mtool\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[2muser$agent$line-summarizer\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[2"]
